id: pm-e48i
title: Package install fallback hints and extension collision plans
description: "Bundle GitHub issues #133 and #134 under package-platform maturity: improve npm package install recovery for unpublished packages with deterministic fallback hints, and add machine-readable collision planning to extension diagnostics/explore so agents can resolve multi-package overlaps with less context. Duplicate check: pm search for unpublished npm install fallback and collision-aware extension profiles found only closed historical package-platform items, no open implementation item."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[6]: agent-ux,"area:extensions","area:packages","area:sdk",github-issue-133,github-issue-134
created_at: "2026-06-07T05:03:46.374Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T05:15:47.784Z"
author: codex-impl-20260607
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: Delivered deterministic package-install recovery and extension collision planning for agent package workflows.
expected_result: Agents receive compact machine-readable recovery hints for unpublished npm package installs and deterministic collision remediation plans for multi-package extension overlaps.
actual_result: npm 404 JSON errors now preserve fallback_candidates and next_best_command end-to-end; package doctor triage now includes collision_plan with ranked deactivate candidates and feature-loss hints; docs and tests cover both behaviors.
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-07T05:03:54.475Z",codex-impl-20260607,"Orientation evidence: no open PRs; open GitHub issues #133/#134 map to this package-platform task; recent main CI/Docs/CodeQL success on f8d9f31a; pnpm audit --audit-level low reports no known vulnerabilities; pnpm outdated shows commander 15 latest but wanted/current 14.0.3, keeping out of scope due Node support history."
  "2026-06-07T05:15:08.709Z",codex-impl-20260607,"Implementation evidence: added npm 404 classification for npm:<name> installs with JSON recovery.fallback_candidates and recovery.next_best_command; added structured triage.collision_plan for extension registration collisions with deterministic deactivate candidates and feature-loss hints; preserved command-specific recovery during CLI error enrichment; documented package-source fallback and collision_plan JSON diagnostics. Sub-agent evidence: GitHub/security lane found no open PRs, current main CI/Docs/CodeQL green, no open Dependabot/code-scanning/secret/advisory alerts, pnpm audit clean, commander@15 blocked by Node engine; SDK/package-author lane recommended pm-e48i as the non-duplicate canonical item for #133/#134."
  "2026-06-07T05:15:09.041Z",codex-impl-20260607,"Verification evidence: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts tests/unit/error-guidance.spec.ts passed (3 files, 80 tests); pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm build passed; pnpm contracts:check passed; pnpm quality:static passed; pnpm security:scan passed; pnpm audit --audit-level low reported no known vulnerabilities; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed at 2531 tests with 100% statements/branches/functions/lines; manual isolated temp smoke at /tmp/pm-e48i-smoke-cQqRP5 passed init, npm 404 JSON fallback assertions, and health --check-only --summary --json. pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift reported history_drift ok and pre-existing resolution metadata warnings on older closed items."
